# Caesar Cipher (Python)

A simple Python program that allows you to encode and decode messages using the classic Caesar Cipher technique.
Shift letters in the alphabet to encrypt or decrypt text.

# Features

Encode (encrypt) messages by shifting letters forward

Decode (decrypt) messages by shifting letters backward

Wraps around the alphabet using modulo arithmetic

Allows repeated execution without restarting the program

Clean and beginner-friendly Python code structure

# How It Works

Run the program

Input:

Choose `encode` or `decode`

Enter your message (lowercase letters)

Enter the shift number

The program:

Adjusts the shift direction based on encode or decode

Shifts each letter in the message by the given number

Wraps letters that exceed the alphabet range

Displays the final encoded or decoded result

Asks whether the user wants t

